 often well-meaning, non-Natives they encounter—some who do not realize Native Americans still exist, much less that they speak English, have cell phones, use the Internet, and might attend powwows and power lunches. Indian Voices, an inspiring and important contribution to the literature about the original Americans, will make every reader rethink the past—and present—of the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aArtichoker, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaheshone, Harrison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerens, Rosemary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrooks Sweeney, Pamela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCraig, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCummings Jacobs, Mary Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeon, Ansel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDucheneaux, Heath, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrank, Henry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrejo, Marcus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeorge, Emma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuy, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHill, Darwin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHomer, Elizabeth Lohah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKa’upu, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLocklear, Curt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewell, Darre